HEADWORD: Ichthyosaurus
<hw>Ich`thy*o*sau"rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Ichthyosauri</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'ichqy`s</grk>, <grk>-y`os</grk>, a fish +
<grk>say^ros</grk> a lizard.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct
genus of marine reptiles; -- so named from their short, biconcave
vertebr⟦ae⟧, resembling those of fishes. Several species, varying in
length from ten to thirty feet, are known from the Liassic, O⟦oum⟧litic,
and Cretaceous formations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

